</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B291B68B9E54FF846DEAFE013675C6DB" box="[151,1359,475,501]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="FA34E5009E54FF846DEAFE013675C6DB" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,501]" box="[151,1359,475,501]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<emphasis id="C8FF39129E54FF846DEAFE013222C6DB" bold="true" box="[151,280,475,501]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name derives from that of Nyanga National Park (
<figureCitation id="62B0F9859E54FF846EF4FE0130EEC6DB" box="[905,980,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1732,1756]" captionTargetBox="[218,1348,948,1674]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 30. Zimbabwe, Mt. Nyanga, Brachystegia woodlands (photo W. Mey)." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">fig. 30</figureCitation>
) where the species was collected.
</paragraph>
